Printing Stars '*' in Pyramid Shape

Input Format

Read n value

Constraints

1<=n<=10^7

Output Format

Printing Stars '*' in Pyramid Shape

Sample Input 0

5
Sample Output 0

    * 
   * * 
  * * * 
 * * * * 
* * * * * 
Sample Input 1

10
Sample Output 1

         * 
        * * 
       * * * 
      * * * * 
     * * * * * 
    * * * * * * 
   * * * * * * * 
  * * * * * * * * 
 * * * * * * * * * 
* * * * * * * * * * 

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int i,j,k,n;
    scanf("%d",&n);
    for(i=1;i<=n;i++){
        for(k=i;k<=n-1;k++)
            printf(" ");
        for(j=1;j<=i;j++){
            printf("* ");
        }
        printf("\n");
    }

    /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT */    
    return 0;
}

